{"title":"Useful keyboard shortcuts for working at a PC","description":"The most useful keyboard shortcuts that can increase your computer speed to a higher level. Keyboard shortcuts for Windows, keyboard shortcuts for working with text, Keyboard shortcuts for creating a screenshot","content":"Hotkeys are a salvation for most PC users, because it is thanks to them that a significant part of the time is saved when working at the computer. In this article, you will learn about the most useful keyboard shortcuts that can increase your computer speed to a higher level. \r\n\r\nBe sure to look at our prepared list, even if you are sure that you know at least half of the combinations available here. You never know, there is something that you could use in your daily life.\r\nAnd be aware that using hotkeys is guaranteed to reduce the time that you can now use in vain, for example, any action performed using the mouse.\r\n\r\n## Keyboard shortcuts for Windows\r\nBasically, these are keyboard shortcuts for working with text, but there are various keyboard shortcuts that are a complete replacement for similar actions performed with the mouse. \r\n\r\nWe advise you to learn how to use them and then working with the text will become incredibly easy and pleasant for you. \r\n\r\n### Working with text\r\n\r\n| Keyboard shortcuts | Description |\r\n| - | - |\r\n| `Ctrl + C` | Copy selection to clipboard (text, images, etc.) |\r\n| `Ctrl + X` | Cut selection to Clipboard |\r\n| `Ctrl + V` | Pasting content from the clipboard |\r\n| `Ctrl + A` | Select everything (all text, the whole page, select all files in the folder...) |\r\n| `Ctrl + Z` | Canceling an action |\r\n| `Ctrl + Y` | Repeat the canceled action |\r\n| `Ctrl + Shift` | Switch keyboard layout |\r\n| `Home` | Move the cursor to the beginning of the line (or select the first file in the directory) |\r\n| `End` | Move the cursor to the end of the line (or highlight the last file in the directory) |\r\n| `Ctrl + ←→` | Move the cursor to the beginning/end of the next/previous word |\r\n| `Ctrl + Shift + ←→` | Move the cursor to the beginning/end of the next/previous word and add it to the selection. Helps to highlight text very quickly |\r\n| `Shift + ←→` | Move the cursor to the previous/next line and add this to the selection |\r\n| `Shift + ↑↓` | Move the cursor to the previous/next character and add it to the selection |\r\n| `Windows + V` | Open the clipboard history (contains all the information recently added to the clipboard, allows you to switch between each other) |\r\n\r\n### Interaction with directories\r\n\r\n| Keyboard shortcuts | Description |\r\n| - | - |\r\n| `Ctrl + D (or Delete)` | Delete a file in a folder |\r\n| `Ctrl + R (or F5)` | Refresh window contents (refresh tab) |\r\n| `Ctrl + Shift + N` | Create a new folder |\r\n| `Backspace` | They will go up to the catalog above |\r\n| `Ctrl + N` | Open the current directory in a new window (several dialog boxes will be opened) |\r\n| `F3` | Search in the catalog (or on the website) |\r\n| `Alt + ←→` | Action back/forward. Previous/The next page in the history of the site or catalog |\r\n| `Alt + Enter` | Display the properties window of the selected file |\r\n\r\n### Opening system windows\r\n\r\n| Keyboard shortcuts | Description |\r\n| - | - |\r\n| `Ctrl + Shift + Esc` | Open the Task Manager |\r\n| `Ctrl + Esc` | Open the Start menu |\r\n| `F2` | Rename the selected file (or item) |\r\n| `F11` | Expand to full screen/Collapse into a small window |\r\n| `Windows + D` | Display/Hide desktop |\r\n| `Windows + E` | Open the Explorer folder |\r\n| `Windows + L` | Account adjustment (change) |\r\n| `Windows + I` | Open the Options menu |\r\n| `Windows + R` | Open the Run window |\r\n| `Windows + S` | Open the Search window |\r\n| `Windows + Pause/Break` | Open System Properties |\r\n\r\n### Interaction with windows\r\n\r\n| Keyboard shortcuts | Description |\r\n| - | - |\r\n| `Windows + M` | Minimize all windows |\r\n| `Windows + Shift + M` | Restore minimized Windows |\r\n| `Windows + ↑↓' ` Expand/Minimize Window |\r\n| `Windows + ←→` | Move the window to the left/right side of the screen |\r\n| `Windows + ← → + ↑↓` | Move the window to the left/right upper/lower corner of the screen |\r\n| `Shift +` Pressing the taskbar button | Open another instance of the application in a new window |\r\n| `Alt + TAB` | Switching between active windows |\r\n| `Alt + F4 (Ctrl +W)` | Close the current window |\r\n| `Alt + Space` | Open the context menu of the current window |\r\n\r\n### Creating screenshots\r\n\r\n| Keyboard shortcuts | Description |\r\n| - | - |\r\n| `PrtScn` | Create a snapshot and add it to the clipboard |\r\n| `Alt + PrtScn` | Create a snapshot of only the current window and add it to the clipboard |\r\n| `Windows + Shift + S` | Create a screenshot of a part of the screen (you can select an area) |"}